    "description": "<p ><em style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Prerequisite: 3rd level</em></p>\n<p ><span class=\"fontstyle1\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle2\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\"><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">Using a reflective object, such as an ordinary mirror or the smooth surface of water, you can commune with your patron or their emissary. You may do so during a short or long rest, receiving or conveying information related to your master&rsquo;s bidding. This entity may also use such surfaces to bridge communication with you on its own terms.<br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" /><br style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\" />You can also use this feature to cast&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle3\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">augury&nbsp;</span><span class=\"fontstyle0\" style=\"box-sizing: border-box; user-select: text;\">without spending spell points. Casting the spell in this way does not require material components, although you do need a reflective surface by which your patron might appear to you. Once you cast the spell in this way, you cannot do so again until you finish a long rest.</span></span></span></span></p>",
